         <ce:floats>
            <ce:figure id="fig0005">
               <ce:label>Fig. 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0005">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0005" view="all">Map of the Białowieża Forest in Poland, illustrating areas with different strategies: Strict Reserves (SR), Nature Reserves (NR), and Managed Forests (MF). The selected study plots, categorized by species composition, are marked with filled circles: broadleaved (green), coniferous (red), and mixed (yellow).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0005" role="short">Fig. 1</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0005" locator="gr1" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725004955/gr1"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0010">
               <ce:label>Fig. 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0010">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0010" view="all">Workflow for assessing species diversity of canopy trees (Hypothesis 1) and all trees (Hypothesis 2) using high-resolution remote sensing datasets.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0010" role="short">Fig. 2</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0010" locator="gr2" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725004955/gr2"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0015">
               <ce:label>Fig. 3</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0015">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0015" view="all">Comparison of Hill numbers (Richness <ce:italic>q</ce:italic>=0, Shannon <ce:italic>q</ce:italic>=1, Simpson <ce:italic>q</ce:italic>=2) illustrating the relationship between canopy tree diversity of field measurements (FM) and remote sensing (RS) across different species composition (BS, CS, and MS) and management categories (SR, NR, and MF).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0015" role="short">Fig. 3</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0015" locator="gr3" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725004955/gr3"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0020">
               <ce:label>Fig. 4</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0020">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0020" view="all">Comparison of Hill numbers (Richness: <ce:italic>q</ce:italic>=0, Shannon: <ce:italic>q</ce:italic>=1, Simpson: <ce:italic>q</ce:italic>=2) illustrating the relationship between canopy tree diversity assessed through field measurements (FM, orange lines) and remote sensing estimates (RS, blue lines) across different species compositions (BS, CS, and MS) and management categories (SR, NR, and MF) (left panel). The right panel shows the relationship between the diversity of all trees, combining FM (orange lines) and RS (blue lines).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0020" role="short">Fig. 4</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0020" locator="gr4" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725004955/gr4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0025">
               <ce:label>Fig. 5</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0025">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0025" view="all">Bland-Altman agreement analysis comparing field measurements (FM) and remote sensing (RS) for estimating species diversity of canopy trees across different species compositions (BS, CS, and MS) and management categories (SR, NR, and MF) (upper panel). The lower panel compares FM and RS for the diversity of all trees.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0025" role="short">Fig. 5</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0025" locator="gr5" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725004955/gr5"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="fig0030">
               <ce:label>Fig. 6</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0030">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0030" view="all">Comparison of relative abundance curves (RACs) for all species, derived from both field measurements (blue lines) and remote sensing (red lines), across varying species compositions (BS, CS, and MS) and management categories (SR, NR, and MF).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0030" role="short">Fig. 6</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0030" locator="gr6" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112725004955/gr6"/>
            </ce:figure>
         </ce:floats>
